Kaelen’s heart ached with profound pity. He longed to nurture the fallen creature, but the obsidian was too hard for the seed to penetrate. In an act of profound sacrifice, Kaelen shattered his perfect tranquility, grinding his massive, solid body into billions of tiny fragments. He scattered his essence across the plains, creating the first rich, yielding soil. The soft earth allowed the Star-Seed to take root and bloom safely.

The gods, awestruck by his selfless dissolution, decreed that Kaelen would live on as the fertile ground, eternally nurturing life.

